      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;welcome&#34;&gt;Welcome&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am a final-year Computer Science student with a deep interest in cybersecurity. Over the past two years, I’ve spent my time outside of class building a practical foundation in offensive security, moving from solving labs to understanding how real networks are secured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;my-background&#34;&gt;My Background&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While my university coursework gave me a strong computer science base, my passion for security led me to pursue the HTB Certified Penetration Testing Specialist (CPTS). Passing this exam was a major milestone for me. It was a rigorous, multi-day assessment that taught me the importance of patience, methodology, and clear reporting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
